76561198058515870,Recommended,547900,28148096,"Posted: 2 December, 2016",all,dbdonlon,"I've played the FOF games for years and they've always been great in every way except one -- presentation.  If you have to have nice graphics, or really any graphics, then this is not the game for you.  But if what you want is a deep and accurate simulation of NFL football, then this is the only game in town.Among the new features, my favorite by far is the updated log.  It now spells out everything about the play, who was in at what position, and even gives a grade for each player.  It's a magnificent addition that allows you to evaluate how your players are playing throughout the game.  It is almost certaily possible for someone to make a graphical viewer using the information given in the log that would dsiplay at the very least what the formations looked like and highlight who did well and who didn't.  If such a thing were added to Solevision it would finally make that feature useful for me.A feature I'm not quite as keen on, at least not yet, is gameplanning.  I usually want to play as GM anyway, but if I were to want to try my hand at coaching, making a plan is too laborious a process as it stands right now.  It needs some streamlining before it's user friendly enough for anyone who approaches it casually.  Fortunately, the game makes fine gameplans on its own.And this is reminding me of another of my favorite new features.  It's such a small thing, but it makes a big difference.  Coaches now have styles.  It's no longer so easy as hiring the best young coach you can -- he also needs to fit your team.  Or, if he's too good to pass up, you'll need to make changes in your team to accomodate his style.And of course the best part of the game is its ability to generate decades of NFL-realistic stats as you play.  I have never seen a more accurate NFL sim than the FOF series, and I think this one is probably the best one yet.I'm stoked about the new release and look forward to many years of enjoyment.  And oh yeah -- one thing that's easy to overlook about this game is how well supported it is by its developer.  It was only just released last week and we've already had the first patch, which fixed all the issues that I had any trouble with.  The developer also likes to surprise us with updates (for free!) whenever he has something new.  This can be something as simple as a roster update, to even including major new features.  I'm not promising unannounced new features will happen but I can tell you that they have happened before.  Other developers would make you pay for your yearly updates.  Solecismic won't promise them -- or even really let you know they are likely to come.  But when they do you'll just wake upone day and have them.So I recommed this game and its developer wholeheartedly.  If you like sports text sims that are accurate and realistic, you can't do better than this one."
