,Not Recommended,547900,29049932,Posted: 5 January,all,Angry Bob,"Other reviews have gone over what's good with the game and I concur with those reviews.Here's why I ultimately can't recommend it.  Let's talk rosters. Each player is graded on a scale from 1 to 9, with 1 being a scrub, and 9 being a rare Superstar.  So the game ranks all the players, but their individual attributes are NOT ranked, only their overall skill.  Example: If Todd Gurley has a grade of 7 the game will randomly determine his individual attributes based on that 7.  We know that Gurley is a bruiser with average speed.  When you start your league, however, the game may look at that 7 and determine that Gurley's actually got 9 out of 9 speed and 4 out of 9 tackle breaking ability. It's completely random every time you start a new league.You can manually override this randomisation and assign the attributes you desire (at least in single player mode), but there's no in-game option to do so, you first have to export a player.csv file and then edit a spreadsheet using Excel and then import your newly edited file into the game. To make matters worse, the spread sheet is highly abbreviated forcing you to consult a legend frequently to make edits.Additionally, many of the game's overall grades for players seemed way off.  Example: Aaron Rodgers was a 5 out of 9 while Brady was an 8 out of 9.  Vic Beasley, who just led the league in sacks, was a 2 out of 9.  I tried a fantasy draft and it had Carlos Dunlap as the best overall player in the league while some of the elite players like JJ Watt were average at best.  And this is all due to the randomization.The rookie draft was also odd.  There's not a way to scout players manually.  Instead, your coaching staff's ""Scouting Ability"" attribute determines the accuracy of the grades that the potential draftees get.  There's no other way to ensure you're drafting good players that I could see.The UI is another negative.   It's drab and unintuitive.  Small font and abbreviations for nearly everything make it a chore to navigate.  I also never found an easy solution to organizing the depth chart or making substitutions.  I'm sure the feature exists somewhere, but I was nearing the 2 hour mark of the game I didn't want to go over my time limit so that I could ensure the refund.Hate giving this a thumbs down, as there's nothing else like it out there, but it needs massive changes to it's logic with rosters and UI to be enjoyable."
