76561198018605511,Recommended,547900,30273075,Posted: 1 March,all,PikeStance,"I owned both Front Office Football 7 and now 8.The game has been improved. You can now choose to run multiple realistic offensive formations and choose your own defensive plays. You have more options on defense to change your preferred personnel. It is disappointing that you can no longer set a depth chart for each personnel grouping. Another criticism of the playbook is that you can only randomly choose your plays. The idea is, you have to choose up to 100 plays out of 200, but you do not choose the 100. Instead, you have to change the ""threshold"" value and it chooses the 100 out of the 200. If you do not like a play, you have to change each part of the play. You are not given a bank of plays to choose from. So unles you want to try every variation on your own, then you stuck with using the ""threshold"" feature. Later when choose which plays to run in each game situation, it is much easier to manage because you can then choose from, the bank of 100 plays chosen in the previous stage of the game.Criticism of the MP aspect. The game system may be fine when playing as a single player because you can act as a coach during the game and make decisions yourself. In MP the games are sim, so you are at the mercy of the coaches you had chosen. Why is this problem? Coaches are key as a GM, but yet, there are very little attributes you can choose from a coach. In FOF7, you can choose the percentage of run to pass plays in a given circumstance. In FOF8, that percentage is no longer present. It is based on the plays you have listed for a given situation and most will have a combination of run to pass unless you set it up differently. it would be different if the game added position coaches and more attributes for the coaches it does include, so that you can make a better decisions on how you want your coaches to conduct the games.Another criticism is drafting. You get a grade and given a rough sketch on the players ability. You can ""interview"" players, but you only have 12 you can perform. The interview only marginally make it more define. It would be nice have the players colloege performances as well. More interviews and more information to help you make a better decision or bad one. LOLAnother change I would like to see is the ability to sign players when I am above the salary cap. Sounds weird, but I like to be able to bring ion guys and then make a decision later. I thought teams can be over until a certain point anyway. It is miner (no I took over a team in a poor financial situation..LOL)I would reccomend playing the game in MP. It is infinitly more fun. Without MP, I think I may fine this game too dull. MOP games are not that time consuming with the exception of the draft and early set up of your team.I know what I wrote makes the game seem unenjoyable, but believe me it is enjoyable to play. Very adictive and fun. If you like football and is critical of your teams choices in the front office, then this is the game for you. If you like pla calling and don't mind SP, then this is a game for you. Way better and more realistic than Madden for sure.Pike"
