,Not Recommended,547900,29368076,Posted: 19 January,all,Twist_28712,"Would be kinda fun if the UI wasn't crap and the player ranking wasn't junk.To give you an idea of how bad the player rankings are, in the game I started, the top 5 QBs in the league were in order: Andy Dalton, Tom Brady, Blake Bortles, Jay Cutler, Matt Stafford.Players like Aaron Rodgers, Drew Brees, and Eli Manning were somwhere near the middle with Josh McCown and Fitzpatrick.The game randomizes players attributes, thus giving some mediocre starters elite skills while killing some very good players skills and making them mediocre.The UI's problem is that everything has a weird name.  Want to see your Depth Chart, yeah that's called Offensive/Defensive Staff.  Along with that confusion is the help system, which doesn't explain anything other than definitions of words.  I wanted to know how to sign players in Free Agency since no players show up in my free agency window, so I looked up Free Agency in the help, all it told me was how to open the free agent window and that free agency is where I could sign players.You can edit the rosters in a very time consuming manner of exporting the player file, opening it up in Excel, editing players, then starting a new game using the edited player file.  And you can spend many hours trying to figure out the frustrating layout of the UI.  I can not recommend this game, because of these flaws it makes it a lot of work and not much fun."
