76561197978866994,Recommended,547900,35505638,Posted: 5 October,all,Azrael,"Ever sat in front of the TV, maybe even watching the NFL Draft and thought ""Why do they draft that guy? I would've made a better choice!""?Ever imagined yourself making gameplans, yelling at players in a locker room but in the real life you never made it to a coaching position in the NFL?Ever wanted to manage a professional football franchise?Then this game is for you. It goes into depth with stats, factors influencing revenue of your stadium, scouting, making gameplans, plays and so on and so on.If you're an expert, you should have no problems getting into the game, if you're more the average fan, who knows the basic concepts of American Football but not more, you should read some articles on Wikipedia, but that should suffice.I strongly recommend playing this game in multiplayer, other human GM's are priceless to have, they can help noobs and, well they act like humans. No AI Manager can substitute this.But if you don't want to play in MP, this game has a SP mode, even with the real NFL players if you like.Ever wanted TB12 and Beastmode in one team? Go ahead, do it!Although this game could explain a lot more, so you don't have to look at Wikipedia in the first place, this is only a minor flaw, regarding the fact, that there aren't that many American Football management games."
